l more. This volume may, therefore, be of interest to those institutions contemplating the founding of such scholarly publishing departments. It may also help to explain to some of those directly concerns with the founding of such presses, and to the general public, what university press publishing is about. Then, too, comparatively little has been issued about publishing in Canada, and very little indeed about scholarly publishing in this country. This volume may, therefore, make a modest contribution to the economic and cultural history of the last sixty years in Canada. It is hoped further that this account of one of the departments of the University of Toronto may be of interest to its faculty and alumni of today, and useful to its historians of tomorrow.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Books & Reading.2bisacsh1 aBohne, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, George W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarden, J. G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGurney, Roy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalpenny, Francess, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarman, Eleanor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarman, Eleanor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJeanneret, Marsh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKurschenska, Harold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarshall, Hilary S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlewman, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toro